Package: billmillr
Title: Rethinking the Bill Miller Problem
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Matthew", "Hoff", , "matthew.g.hoff@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package calculates the likelihood that any one trader
    out of n traders will beat the market in at least a k-years sequence
    out of a t-years time period by considering independent and definite
    start and stop periods of such a k-years sequence given a t-years
    time period for the nth trader.
